title: Ninja Mountain Bike Performance | Mulberry Gap, Georgia
Nestor Cup Prologue
description: First race of the popular Nestor Cup Series. Bring out your roadie for a Merckx style time trial. Join us for one race or the entire series.
course: Approx. 3 mile time trial on the Hutchinson Island race track.
registration: Register online or on site day of the race. $15 preregistration, $20 day of race
notes: 1st- $35, 2nd- 25, 3rd- 20, 4th- 15, 5th- 10 Timing chip rental $5, may use own chip
directions: Follow I-16 East to Exit 166 (Gwinnett & Louisville Road, Charleston) go over Talmadge Bridge, Stay in right lane and turn right at base of the bridge onto Hutchinson Island, Follow signs to Trade & Convention Center, All parking is at the convention center. Turn right out of parking lot and left towards passed the golf club to the course.

title: 21st Annual Mountain Ranger Race @ Camp Merrill
Scott Bicycles Mountain Bike Time Trials
Specialty Paint & Body Gambler Ride p/b Georgia Cycle Sport
'79 Twilight: The Twilight That Never Happened
description:
Riders, start your pedals!  79' Twilight is upon us! This disco-era bike relay will put your team of three battling others through a series of obstacles while rushing down Athens' infamous Clayton Street.   Not enough of a challenge you say? So did we. The bike you are riding will act as a relay stick where you will need to not only get to the finish line in the quickest time, but also pass on the bike to your next teammmate. All 3 members must successfully cross the finish line to be qualified. This bracket style competition will come with excitement, sportsmanship, and of course a few unforeseen bumps along the road.

Sign up your team now under RSVP, the prize will make it all worth it! See you and your bell bottoms at 8:00pm at the starting line
course: 300 meter loop, obstacles, disco-era garb encourage
registration:
Register your team using the RSVP button:
https://79twilighttheracethatneverw.splashthat.com

title: 2017 Jekyll Island Ride
description: Annual 4th of July Ride to Jekyll (on the 1st). 90 miles from Pooler to Jekyll Island where you can enjoy the beach, the water park, or just hang out.
course:
90 miles on highway 17 to 99, to 17, to the Jekyll Island causeway.
Two groups- 18 - 20 mph and 20 - 23 mph speed will be controlled.
registration: No registration is necessary but you must sign a waiver and wear a helmet.
notes: We have rented a bus for the return trip to Pooler with room for about 20 people. Cost is $30 per person. Bus leaves Jekyll at 5:00pm
directions: Meet at the Lowes parking lot on Pooler Parkway at 6:30am

title: Team Novo Nordisk Talent ID Camp #2
Grant Park Category State Crit Championship
PAAL's Criterium Age Group State Championships
GACX @  Boundary Waters Park  P/B Smyrna Bicycles
Ninja Mountain Bike Performance | Mulberry Gap (GA1013)
description:
Surrounded by some of the best mountain bike trails in the southeast. Pinhoti, Bear Creek, Mountaintown Creek, Windy Gap, Tibbs and Milma, – as well as scenic forest service roads which connect trail options – all can be ridden out of our driveway.

It’s time to take your skills to a whole new level.

This camp is designed for the enthusiast rider or avid racer that is looking to build up and clean up their ‘toolbox’ of mountain bike skills in order to handle a variety of terrain at speed.
course: We will blend an in-depth version of our traditional Intermediate / Advanced skills training with coached riding sessions.
